SIMPLE: junketing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Junketing
<hw>Jun"ket*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A feast or
entertainment; a revel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All those snug <qex>junketings</qex> and public gormandizings for
which the ancient magistrates were equally famous with their modern
successors.</q> <rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The apostle would have no reveling or <qex>junketing</qex> upon
the altar.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or process of taking a junket{3}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Junketries</ent>⟦br⟧
